    public interface QualifiedIdentifierProxy
extends IdentifierProxy

    A qualified identifier, such as module.part. Qualified identifiers are generated by the compiler to identify entities within an instantiated module. They consist of a base identifier (module in the above example), and a component identifier (part).

    The component identifier may be a qualified identifier in itself, while the base identifier should only be a simple identifier (SimpleIdentifierProxy) or an indexed identifier (IndexedIdentifierProxy).
